"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-08-paris-2024-olympics-nigeria-4x100m-relay-teams-crash-out\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria had a disappointing outing in the 4x100m relays at the ongoing 2024 Olympic Games on Thursday morning.  The men's 4\\u00d7100 quartet of Favour Ashe, Kanyinsola Ajayi, Alaba Akintola and Usheoritse Itsekiri finished 7th in heat 1.  The quartet however ran a season's best time of 38.20s.  USA won the race in a time of 37.47s, while South Africa finished second with a time of 37.94s.  The women's 4\\u00d7100 team also failed to make it to the final.  The quartet of Justina Eyakpobeyan, Favour Ofili, Rosemary Chukwuma and Tima Godbless finished 6th in heat 2.  They ran a season's best time of 42.70s.  Paris 2024 Olympics: Adekuroye advances into women's freestyle wrestling quarter-finals  EPL: Xabi Alonso names three teams that will compete for title  Dantata gives reasons some Western nations equip bandits in Nigeria  Turkey: Victor Osimhen leaves Galatasaray, returns to Nigeria after injury  Super Eagles: Why I chose Nigeria over Germany - Maduka Okoye  Nigeria, UK seal agreements on migration, border security, business visas  Nigeria, Vietnam have highest fuel price hikes worldwide amid Iran, US-Israel war  ACF calls for overhaul of Nigeria's security strategy amid rising terror attacks  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"